cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a novel method for classification and biomarker selection for ASD using deep learning methods, specifically invertible networks. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The method uses fMRI data, which involves image processing (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) to some extent. The paper also discusses the interpretability of the model, which is a current topic of interest in the field of AI (cs.AI). Overall, the paper's focus on deep learning, classification, and interpretability suggests that it is most likely to belong to cs.LG, followed by cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
